  "text": "It is interesting to compare the performance results of this implementation to the one in [CITATION_1] , which has a reported throughput of 1.15 Gbit/s and uses a code over GF(64). We note that AMSA-256 GF(64) implementation achieves the same throughput at an SNR of approximately 3.1 dB, even though the clock frequency in this case is much lower. Additionally, the error correction performance in [CITATION_2] is good in the 3.2-3.6 dB SNR range, but very limited in the 2.0-2.4 dB range used in this work.",
